title: Aliki Georgiou goes missing from Sydney
text:
Aliki Georgiou was reported missing after leaving her home in Victoria on Monday without telling her family were she was going

A desperate search is underway to find a 26-year-old woman last seen leaving a home in Sydney's eastern suburbs.

Aliki Georgiou was reported missing after leaving her home in Victoria on Monday without telling her family were she was going.

Her family later learned that she was seen at a home in Darling Point, in Sydney, on Thursday.

Ms Georgiou was seen leaving the unit on Yarranabbe Road at about 11am in a black Toyota Corolla with the Victorian registration 1PM6PS.

She is believed to have been heading to Brisbane and had a dog with her.

Police say she has a medical condition.

Ms Georgiou is white, of medium build and is 165cm tall with brown hair.

Anyone who sees her is urged to contact the police.
